The Vice President of the United States had a teleconference with astronauts at the Johnson Space Center in Houston, Texas. She expressed her excitement to be part of the Space Council and her admiration for the work being done in space. The astronauts talked about their unique perspective of seeing Earth from the International Space Station, with no borders and a sense of unity among humanity. They also discussed the importance of taking care of the Earth and how their research on the space station can be applied to benefit life on Earth, such as improving food security and understanding immune cell aging. The Vice President asked the astronauts for advice to inspire students to pursue studies in space and science.